.TH HSH 1 "April 2026" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command language interpreter that reads commands
from standard input or from a file and executes them.

The shell operates in two modes:
.TP
Interactive mode
When started without arguments and connected to a terminal.
.TP
Non-interactive mode
When input is piped or redirected.

.SH USAGE
Start the shell by typing:
.B ./hsh

Then enter commands like:
.TP
.B /bin/ls
List directory contents
.TP
.B /bin/pwd
Print current working directory

.SH FUNCTIONALITY
The shell:
.TP
- Displays a prompt in interactive mode
- Reads user input
- Executes commands using execve
- Waits for child processes to terminate

.SH RETURN VALUE
The shell returns 0 on success.

.SH ERRORS
If a command is not found, an error message is displayed.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Interactive mode:
.nf
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
file1 file2
($)
.fi

.TP
Non-interactive mode:
.nf
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
file1 file2
.fi

